  "prompt": "What do people of Pakistan Occupied Kashmir think about India?",
  "response": "The perspectives of people in Pakistan-Occupied Kashmir (PoK) towards India are complex and varied. Generally, opinions can be divided into different groups:\n\n1. Pro-Pakistan Perspective:\n- Many support Pakistan's stance\n- View India as an occupying power\n- Believe Kashmir should be part of Pakistan\n- Support the Pakistani government's position\n\n2. Pro-Independence Perspective:\n- Some locals desire complete independence from both Pakistan and India\n- Want self-determination and freedom from external control\n- Criticize both countries' policies\n\n3. Pro-India Perspective:\n- A minority group sympathizes with India\n- Believe Indian democratic system is more stable\n- Want better economic opportunities\n\n4. General Sentiments:\n- Many feel politically marginalized\n- Frustrated with limited political rights\n- Concerned about economic development\n- Experience restricted freedom of expression\n\n5. Regional Variations:\n- Attitudes differ across different regions of PoK\n- Urban and rural populations have different perspectives\n- Economic conditions influence political views\n\nIt's important to note that these are generalized observations, and individual opinions can vary significantly. The region's complex political history and ongoing territorial dispute contribute to diverse viewpoints.",
